1. b3
{ We just give Black the centre, and a false sense of security... only to take all of it back with interest at the right time! }
1... e5
{ After  1...d6  2.Bb2  Black is well advised to transpose to 1...e5 territory! }
2. Bb2
{ The fight is already beginning. Black has to make a decision on how to defend the pawn. }
2... Nc6 3. c4
{ Inspired by Fischer's direction, we fight for the control of the central square on d5. }
3... Nf6
{ Continuing with development and Black is preparing to break with d5. } 4. e3
d5 5. cxd5 Nxd5 6. a3
{ An important move restricting Black's ideas with Ndb4. } 6... Be6
{ Black is trying to go for an English attack! } 7. Qc2 Qd7
{ 7...f6  8.b4  Qd7  will transpose to our mainline here. } 8. Nf3 f6 9. b4
{ Signalling the start of the war! } 9... O-O-O 10. b5 Na5 11. d4
{ Let's show our cards! 😀 } 11... e4 12. Nfd2
{ Bad is  12.Qxe4  Bf5  and we lose the queen. 🙁 } 12... f5 13. Nc3
{ Now we are in France... I mean French territory. We go for short castling and start the queenside assault! 'May the French be with you!' This Nimzo-Larsen is so vast, I am loving it! }
