[Black "The brave and the KID II #3"]
[Result "*"]

1. b3
{ We just give Black the centre, and a false sense of security... only to take all of it back with interest at the right time! }
1... Nf6 2. Bb2 g6 { 'Two can play this game!' } 3. Nf3 Bg7 4. g3
{ We just take it one step further and aim for a double fianchetto! } 4... O-O
5. Bg2
{ This is a major tabiya, there are many ways for Black to continue here. }
5... c5 6. c4
{ Stopping Black from achieving both c5 and d5. It is the essential point in our strategy. }
6... Nc6 7. O-O d6 8. d4
{ Black could try to utilize the pressure along the long diagonal with... }
8... Ne4 9. e3 { This looks stronger than the popular Nbd2. } 9... Bg4 10. Qc1
{ An important tactical point which allows us to get an advantage. } 10... Bxf3
11. Bxf3 Ng5 12. Bxc6
{ Ruining Black's structure...this is one of the advantages of having the bishop! }
12... bxc6 13. dxc5 dxc5
{ If we can beat out Black's initiative... we will have the last laugh 😀 } 14.
Bxg7 Kxg7 15. h4 { There was no point in allowing the knight on g5 anymore. }
15... Ne4 16. Qc2 f5 17. Nc3
{ We have the advantage, thanks to the doubled pawns on c6/c5 who will be a constant source of worry. }
*

