{ We just give Black the centre, and a false sense of security... only to take all of it back with interest at the right time! }
1... Nf6 2. Bb2 g6 { 'Two can play this game!' } 3. Nf3 Bg7 4. g3
{ We just take it one step further and aim for a double fianchetto! } 4... O-O
5. Bg2
{ This is a major tabiya, there are many ways for Black to continue here. }
5... c5 6. c4
{ Stopping Black from achieving both c5 and d5. It is the essential point in our strategy. }
6... Nc6 7. O-O d6 8. d4 cxd4 9. Nxd4 Bd7 10. Nc3 Qa5 11. Nc2
{ Rule breaker in action! The main move has been the undeserving e3. } 11...
Ne4 12. b4 { Breaking the concentration on c3 with this cool tactical blow! }
12... Nxc3 13. Bxc3
{ With an advantage due to the queenside control and the eventual outpost on d5 for our knight. }
