1. b3
{ We just give Black the centre, a false sense of security... Only to take all of them back with interest at the right time! }
1... Nf6 2. Bb2 g6 { 'Two can play this game!' } 3. Nf3 Bg7 4. g3
{ We just take it one step further and aim for a double fianchetto! } 4... O-O
5. Bg2
{ This is a major tabiya, there are many ways for Black to continue here. }
5... d5 6. c4
{ Attacking the centre before Black can comfortably stabilize it. } 6... dxc4
7. bxc4 c5 8. O-O
{ Since we have an extra pawn in the centre, I tend to favour our chances. }
8... Nc6 9. Ne5
{ I like this direction, because most of my opponent's would always take on e5 after which we are just better! The move I faced most was }
9... Nxe5 10. Bxe5 Ne8 11. Bxg7 Kxg7 12. Nc3
{ We are clearly rolling here, due to the insanely powerful catalan bishop and potential targets on the queenside. }
12... Rb8 13. d3 b6 14. Qa4 { Before black can get in Bb7! } 14... a6 15. Rab1
{ With a clear advantage due to the weak pawns on the queenside. } *

