[Result "*"]

1. b3
{ We just give Black the centre with a false sense of security, only to take it all back with interest at the right time! }
1... c5 2. Bb2 Nc6 3. c4
{ The move order is very important, we delay Nf3 for the time being. } 3... Nf6
4. e3
{ 4.Bxf6  gxf6  5.Nc3  with a strategical fight. To be honest I wouldn't mind trying this as White!  5...e6  6.e3  with a pleasant advantage.   5...h5!  Black has to do this, otherwise he gets slightly worse.  6.h4!  Fixing the pawn on h5 and making it a future target for our pieces.  6...d6  7.g3  with play on the light squares. }
4... e6 5. Nf3
{ After  5...d5  6.cxd5  either recapture will lead to the QGD chapter. } 5...
Be7
{ Black is fiddling with the move orders! Somehow I had to revisit many lines which I managed to avoid with the same move tricks 😀... }
6. Nc3
{ Pay close attention to the move order here, as we can avoid some good options for Black. First comes the knight! One of the natural reactions for Black would be }
6... d5 7. cxd5
{ Of course we can't allow Black to achieve d4 followed by e5 which would give him the better chances. }
7... exd5 8. d4 { Same concept, stop d4 by playing d4 ourselves. } 8... O-O 9.
Be2
{ 9...Bg4  shouldn't bother us after  10.dxc5!  Just when things were getting hot around d4.  10...Bxc5  11.O-O  with a stable advantage due to the indirect control over d4. }
9... Ne4
{ Black is preparing Bf6 with nice pressure on d4 and the a1-h8 diagonal. This was my major issue...but finally after huge effort and some music on the side😀, I managed to find a nice line for us! }
10. dxc5
{ We have to aim for some sort of imbalance if we want to get something here.   If we go for  10.O-O  Bf6  is fine for Black and completely equal. }
10... Qa5
{ Black has to play actively otherwise he will end up worse due to the weak and isolated pawn on d5. }
11. Rc1 { You attack bro? I support😀 } 11... Bf6
{ Continuing the pinning attack! } 12. Nd4 { Breaking the pin... } 12... Nxc5
{ The only way for Black. } 13. Nxc6 bxc6
{ Hurray! We have finally managed to change the structure giving Black a weak pawn on c6. }
14. Qd2 { An important move fighting against the return of the knight to e4. }
14... Bf5 15. O-O { Now that Ne4 is not possible, we can safely castle. } 15...
Qb4 16. Qe1 { Preparing some nasty Nd5 ideas! Another direction is } 16... Rfb8
17. Nd1 { Getting ready for the endgame grind. } 17... Qxe1 18. Rxe1 Bxb2 19.
Nxb2 { will just lose a pawn. } *

