1. b3
{ We just give Black the centre with a false sense of security, only to take it all back with interest at the right time! }
1... c5 2. Bb2 Nc6 3. c4
{ The move order is very important, we delay Nf3 for the time being. } 3... Nf6
4. e3
{ 4.Bxf6  gxf6  5.Nc3  with a strategical fight. To be honest I wouldn't mind trying this as White!  5...e6  6.e3  with a pleasant advantage.   5...h5!  Black has to do this, otherwise he gets slightly worse.  6.h4!  Fixing the pawn on  h5  and making it a future target for our pieces.  6...d6  7.g3  with play on the light squares. }
4... b6 5. g3 { We have to insist on the fianchetto at any cost! } 5... e6 6.
Bg2 d5 7. Ne2
{ Another advantage of delaying Nf3, the knight is well placed on e2 and keeps the h1-a8 diagonal free for the use of the bishop. }
7... Bb7 8. cxd5 { Time to take some action in the center. } 8... Nb4
{ Black is trying to use the weakness on d3 and the pin along the h1-a8 diagonal. }
9. Nf4 { Preventing both Nd3+ and Bd5. } 9... Nfxd5 10. O-O Qd7
{ Only move otherwise Black is worse. } 11. Nxd5
{ Since Black was ready for Nf4. } 11... Bxd5 12. Bxd5 Qxd5 13. d4 cxd4 14.
Bxd4
{ Here Black has to embark on a dangerous path in order to equalize...otherwise he is worse. }
14... e5 15. Nc3 Qe6 16. Rc1
{ Cooly giving up the bishop and preparing the nasty Nb5. } 16... exd4 17. Nb5
Rc8 { Only move. } 18. Qf3
{ We have a very dangerous attack for the piece and Black has only two moves with which he can survive. }
18... Nc2 19. Rxc2 { Preparing the Nxd4 fork. } 19... Rxc2 20. Nxd4 Qc8 21.
Qe4+ { Wins back the rook with an extra pawn and a winning advantage. } *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Quickstarter Guide 1.b3"]
[Black "A solid and shanky recipe #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. b3
{ We just give Black the centre with a false sense of security, only to take it all back with interest at the right time! }
1... d5 2. Bb2
{ A slightly tricky and clever move order aimed against our plans would be }
2... Nf6 3. Nf3
{ 3.d3  would be horrible here as Black has many plans he can execute like  3...c5  with advantage and nice control of the dark-squares. }
3... Bf5 4. Nh4 { Let us join together and create a new path ourselves!! } 4...
Bd7 5. c4 { Beginning of the center fight... } 5... e6 6. Nf3 c5 7. e3
{ Preventing d4 ideas. } 7... Nc6 8. cxd5 exd5 9. Be2
{ In our mainlines the bishop would be on c8 which would allow d4 option for Black! Bad is }
9... d4 10. O-O
{ It's important to note that if the bishop was on c8, then we wouldn't be able to castle because of d4-d3 which traps our e2-bishop. }
10... dxe3 11. dxe3 Be7 12. Nc3
{ We are comfortable due to the central majority. } 12... O-O 13. Qc2 Nb4 14.
Qb1
{ Followed by a3-Qc2 with a big advantage due to central pawn majority and our usual unstoppable asset on b2 😀 }
