[White "Quickstarter Guide 1.b3"]
[Black "The Magician's Path #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. b3
{ We just give Black the centre, a false sense of security... Only to take all of them back with interest at the right time! }
1... d5 2. Bb2 Bg4
{ was the preference of my childhood hero-Mikhal Tal. Black is cutting into White's plans of development. }
3. f3
{ We answer in style! One of the hidden advantages of not commiting Nf3! Attacking the bishop and clearing the path for e4. }
3... Bf5 4. e4 { Attacking the centre with maximum force! } 4... dxe4 5. Nc3
{ I love it, when we sacrifice pawns for sake of fast development and intiative! }
5... Nf6 6. g4
{ Making our intentions very clear, we are just gonna roll over the kingside with pawn storms! }
6... Bg6 7. Qe2 { Clearing the path to safety for the king. } 7... Nc6
{ Going for the uncontrolled d4-square. } 8. O-O-O Nd4 9. Qg2
{ The g2-square is ideal for the queen to eye the long diagonal. } 9... exf3
10. Nxf3 Nxf3 11. Qxf3 c6 12. g5 Nh5 13. Bd3
{ Exchanging the light-squares bishop after which the f7-pawn will become a major weakness. }
13... e6 14. Bxg6 hxg6 15. Rhf1 Qd7 16. Ne4
{ with a big advantage as the f7-pawn will be Black's undoing as he can never castle either side! }
*

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Quickstarter Guide 1.b3"]
[Black "The Magician's Path #2"]
[Result "*"]

1. b3
{ We just give Black the centre, a false sense of security... Only to take all of them back with interest at the right time! }
1... d5 2. Bb2 Bg4
{ was the preference of my childhood hero-Mikhal Tal. Black is cutting into White's plans of development. }
3. f3
{ We answer in style! One of the hidden advantages of not commiting Nf3! Attacking the bishop and clearing the path for e4. }
3... Bh5 4. h4
{ Nepo is fighting a lonely battle in this line...Let's also join in on the fun! }
4... f6 { This is the move I faced most in my bullet run. } 5. d4 Qd6
{ Black is targetting the only weakness in our camp - the g3 square. } 6. e3
{ Not fearing the check on g3. } 6... Nc6 7. c4
{ We have no development and we are opening up the game...I am extremely sorry for recommending this move! Comp is insisting on this nonsense and feels this is the way to gain a slight plus. }
7... O-O-O 8. cxd5
{ We have managed to gain a central majority...Is that what we were fighting for? All this time? }
8... Qxd5 9. Nc3 Qd6 10. Ne4
{ Continuing to bully the queen to gain some positional pluses. } 10... Qb4+
{ Only move which doesn't lose immediately due to the huge weakness on e6 and c5. }
11. Bc3 Qa3 12. Bb5
{ Quickly we are catching up with our missing development by targetting Black's pieces. }
12... Be8 { What else? } 13. Qc1
{ After the exchange of queens, we needn't worry about anything in life! }
13... e5 14. Qxa3 Bxa3 15. dxe5 fxe5 { Black has a permanent weakness now. }
16. Rd1 { Skillfully we keep on exchanging pieces which improve our position. }
16... Rxd1+ 17. Kxd1 Nf6 18. Nxf6 { Giving up one advantage to gain another! }
18... gxf6 { The h7-pawn feels lonely instead of e5-pawn :. } 19. Bd3
{ with a very minute pull thanks to the kingside pawn majority. } *

