[Result "*"]

1. b3
{ We just give Black the centre, a false sense of security... Only to take all of them back with interest at the right time! }
1... d5 2. Bb2 c5
{ Black starts the fight for the centre. I came up with the name Ozmin Attack which is just Nimzo put in reverse order thanks to the help of my discord members :. }
3. e3
{ The bishop is usually best placed on b5 in order to fight for the control of the e5-square. }
3... Nf6 { Black can try to be flexible with his plans. } 4. Nf3 Bf5 5. Bb5+
{ Forcing the b8-knight to d7 where it will be slightly misplaced and less active than on c6. }
5... Nbd7 6. O-O { Golden principle No.3: King safety! } 6... e6 7. Nh4
{ Going after the bishop pair. The only game so far went } 7... Bg4 8. Bxf6
{ A nice tactical theme which will win material in many situation. } 8... Qxf6
{ No other choice! } 9. Qxg4 Qxa1 10. Nc3
{ White has winning advantage, Let's take a look at some lines... } 10... Qb2
11. Qa4 Rd8 { 11...O-O-O  12.Qxa7  is also hopeless. } 12. Qxa7 { Greedy VD! }
12... Be7 { Attacking the knight to catch up in development. } 13. Nf3 O-O 14.
Qxb7
{ But unfortunately for Black due to the X-ray on the 7th rank, he is forced to lose a piece giving us a clear advantage. }
