[White "Quickstarter Guide 1.b3"]
[Black "Ozmin Attack #2"]
[Result "*"]

1. b3
{ We just give Black the centre, a false sense of security... Only to take all of them back with interest at the right time! }
1... d5 2. Bb2 c5
{ Black starts the fight for the centre. I came up with the name Ozmin Attack which is just Nimzo put in reverse order thanks to the help of my discord members :. }
3. e3
{ The bishop is usually best placed on b5 in order to fight for the control of the e5-square. }
3... Nc6 4. Bb5
{ Given a choice,we always go for this placement for the bishop as it helps us fight for the e5-square. }
4... e6 5. Bxc6+
{ Before Black changes his mind and protects the knight with a piece :! } 5...
bxc6 { Black's structure will remain like this for a while! } 6. d3 Nf6 7. Nf3
Bd6 8. e4 { Everyone went for Nbd2 or others. } 8... dxe4 9. dxe4 Nxe4 10. Nbd2
{ It is a full fledged pawn sacrifice. } 10... Nxd2 11. Nxd2
{ The knight has two juicy squares on c4 or e4. } 11... O-O 12. Qf3 f6
{ Black can't do without this move...as the b2-bishop was getting too powerful. }
13. O-O-O
{ With fantastic compensation for the pawn and the weak pawns on c5/ c6. It makes sure we will win at least one of them! }
