{ After the exchange of the g7-bishop, the king will be permanently weak due to the potential threats on the long diagonal. }
10. Nc3 { The knight has a nice outpost on d5. } 10... d6 11. Be2
{ The bishop is better placed here as it is away from any attacks of the c6-knight and keeping the d-file open for the use of major pieces. }
11... Be6 12. O-O
{ Is clearly better for White due to the weak king and potential outpost on d5... with play for us on all fronts - the centre, queenside and kingside! }
