[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "The Brave and The Bold: 1.b3 e5 2.Bb2 Nc6"]
[Black "3.c4 d5 #5"]
[Result "*"]

1. b3
{ We just give Black the centre with a false sense of security, only to take it all back with interest at the right time! }
1... e5
{ This is one of the most direct attempts and the most principled way to play against the Nimzo-Larsen.   1...Nc6  2.Bb2  will transpose. }
2. Bb2
{ The fight is already beginning. Black has to make a decision on how to defend the pawn. }
2... Nc6 3. c4
{ Inspired by Fischer's direction, we fight for the control of the central square on d5. }
3... d5
{ Honestly I couldn't believe my eyes when even this was a decent option!! } 4.
cxd5 Qxd5 5. Nc3 Qe6
{ The queen will go to g6...where it will be well placed. 😀 } 6. Rc1
{ A new direction. } 6... Nf6 7. e3 Bd6
{ This was Black's idea of putting the queen on e6. } 8. Nb5
{ It is essential to win the bishop pair. } 8... a6 9. Nxd6+ Qxd6 10. Be2
{ Aimed against Bg4 ideas. } 10... O-O 11. Nf3 Bg4 12. O-O
{ With a nice middlegame due to the two bishops... } 12... e4 13. Nd4 Bxe2 14.
Qxe2
{ Is also very pleasant for us as the bishop will reign supreme and we can open the f-file with the cool break f3! }
