[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "The Brave and The Bold: 1.b3 e5 2.Bb2 Nc6"]
[Black "4.e3 d5 5.cxd5 Nxd5 6.a3 Qf6 #2"]
[Result "*"]

1. b3
{ We just give Black the centre with a false sense of security, only to take it all back with interest at the right time! }
1... e5
{ This is one of the most direct attempts and the most principled way to play against the Nimzo-Larsen.   1...Nc6  2.Bb2  will transpose. }
2. Bb2
{ The fight is already beginning. Black has to make a decision on how to defend the pawn. }
2... Nc6 3. c4
{ Inspired by Fischer's direction, we fight for the control of the central square on d5. }
3... Nf6
{ Continuing with development and Black is preparing to break with d5. } 4. e3
{ We open up the path of the f1-bishop while keeping our development schemes of the knight's hidden for the time being. }
4... d5 5. cxd5 Nxd5 6. a3
{ An important move restricting Black's ideas with Ndb4. } 6... Qf6
{ Mr. ChessBrah Eric Hansen went for this queen shift. } 7. b4
{ Slowly starting the queenside expansion and gaining some space. } 7... Bd6 8.
Nf3 a6 { Super prophylaxis. } 9. d3 O-O 10. Nbd2
{ With ideas like Nc4 or Ne4. } 10... Qg6 11. Rc1
{ Let me show you one sample line: } 11... Be6 12. h4
{ Preparing to annoy the queen with h5. } 12... Bg4 13. Be2 Rad8 14. h5
{ Opening the h-file. } 14... Bxh5 15. Qb3 { Hitting the knight with tempo. }
15... Nf6 16. Rc4
{ Rook shift to the kingside followed by an awesome attack and more than enough compensation for us. }
16... Rfe8 17. Rch4 Bg4
{ Exchanging  17...Bxf3  will simply be met with  18.Bxf3  followed by Nd2-e4 and Ke1-e2 with a good advantage thanks to the pressure along the h-file and the bishop pair which more than compensates for the pawn deficit. }
18. Ne4 Bf8
{ Black can also try  18...Nxe4  where it will be met with a beautiful intermezzo  19.Rxh7!  Kf8   @@StartFEN@@3rr1k1/1pp2ppR/p1nb2q1/4p3/1P2n1b1/PQ1PPN2/1B2BPP1/4K2R b K - 0 19@@EndFEN@@  19...Qxh7  does not help as  20.Rxh7  Kxh7  21.dxe4  gives a big advantage due to the threat of Nf3-g5.  20.dxe4  with a huge advantage for White. }
19. Nxf6+ gxf6 20. Rxh7
{ We have got our pawn back and Black's kingside is completely ruined. } 20...
Bg7 21. R7h2 { With a slight advantage due to Black's weak king. } *

