8. Nf3 Re8 9. Be2
{ We are doing well here, as I feel the rook would be misplaced and jobless on e8.   Once in bullet I went for  9.Nbd2  which allows the stunning  9...Nd4!   N  10.g3  Nxf3+  11.Nxf3  Bg4  12.Bg2  c6  with a more comfortable game for Black... since the d3-e3-g3 set-up doesn't always match well! }
