{ I hope that with my course, I can change the tide and make this the mainline and outlast the fake popularity of Qc2 😀.   The most popular line is  7.Qc2  and I would have loved to recommend it... if only it had worked!  This is the only move that has been covered in Logozar's course:  7...Qe7!  I couldn't find any way to even equalize here 😀. Not something we want to do with our amazing line!  8.Nf3   After  8.d3  f5  Black is slightly better.  8...e4  9.Nd4  Nxd4  10.Bxd4  O-O  maybe White can equalize, but it is not something I would recommend! }
7... O-O
{ It is worth noting that  7...Qg5  8.Nf3  Qg6  9.Nbd2  O-O  which has been mentioned in Mikhalevski's Grandmaster Repertoire: Beating Minor Openings will transpose to our lines from  8...Qf6. }
8. Nf3 Qe7 9. Nbd2 a5
{ 9...f5  would transpose to the mainline of this variation. } 10. Be2 f5 11.
Qc2 { Achieving the hedgehog setup. } 11... Bd7
{ 11...Kh8  12.O-O  would be similar. } 12. O-O Rae8 13. Nc4
{ With a complex reversed Scheveningen type position. } *

