[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "The Brave and The Bold: 1.b3 e5 2.Bb2 Nc6"]
[Black "2.Bb2 Nc6 3.Nf3 Alternative"]
[Result "*"]

1. b3 e5 { 1...Nc6  2.Bb2  will also transpose. } 2. Bb2 Nc6
{ The fabled blitz weapon of Nepo is } 3. Nf3 e4 4. Nd4 Nxd4
{ Bringing the bishop into our line of fire.   4...Qf6  5.e3  Bc5  6.Nc3!  Breaking the pin in style!  6...Nxd4   6...Bxd4  7.exd4  7...Qxd4  Otherwise Black is just gonna have a bad position and we will have the amazing bishop pair.   7...Nge7  8.d5  Opening up the long diagonal.  8...Ne5  9.d6!!  9...Qxd6   9...cxd6  10.Nxe4  10...Qg6  11.Ng3  followed by Be2 and kingside castling with a winning advantage.  10.Nb5  Black queen is completely overloaded and has to defend both c7-pawn and e5 knight.  10...Qc5  11.b4!  With this final deflection, the poor queen on c5 has to accept defeat and has to accept huge material losses.  8.Na4!  A cute discovered attack!  8...Qd6  9.Bxg7  winning the rook on h8 with a killer advantage.  7.Nd5!  A nice intermezzo before taking on d4.  7...Qe5   7...Nf3+  One of the best attempts to muddy the waters!  8.gxf3  Qxb2  9.Nxc7+  Kd8  10.Nxa8  Even though the a8-knight is doomed... the material balance, piece activity, development and safety of king are all in our favor!  8.exd4  Qxd5  Bad is   8...Bxd4  9.Bxd4  Qxd4  10.Nxc7+  winning the a8-rook.  9.dxc5  Black has no time to win the c5-pawn due to the threat of Bxg7.  9...Nf6  10.Qe2!  Continuing to use the superior development to gain the necessary momentum necessary to achieve a solid advantage.  10...Qxc5   10...O-O  11.O-O-O  And we can protect the c5-pawn with either Qc4 or Qe3 next with a clear advantage due to the bishop pair.  11.Bxf6  gxf6  12.Qxe4+  Qe5  13.Qe3!  Making sure that Black is not able to get rid of his horrible doubled pawns on the f-file.  13...O-O  14.d4  14...Qa5+  15.Qd2  Re8+  16.Be2  with a clear advantage and if Black tries to be clever with  16...Qg5  17.h4!  Forcing Qxd2.  17...Qxd2+  18.Kxd2  with a clear advantage in the endgame due to the doubled f-pawns. 1.b3 e5-Minor update }
5. Bxd4 d5
{ It is important to prevent c4 from White.  Once I went for the dubious   5...Nf6  allowing  6.c4!  followed by Nc3 with a very nice middlegame for White.  Also fine for us is   5...c5  6.Bb2  d5  7.e3  Preparing d3 next.  7...Nf6  8.d3  exd3  9.Bxd3  with a slight pull for White in @@StartBracket@@Nepo-Motylev Blitz 2020@@EndBracket@@ }
6. e3 h5
{ A strong move gaining the initiative on the kingside!  It is important not to play tame with moves like   6...Nf6  7.c4!  White gains the upper hand due to the centre pressure!  7...c6  8.Nc3  with a slight pull. }
7. d3 Bf5 { with a better game for Black. } *

