{ After  1...d6  2.Bb2  Black is well advised to transpose to 1...e5 territory! }
2. Bb2 f6
{ In an ideal world, this would be the best reply to the Nimzo-Larsen since Black is using his pawns to reduce the potential of the mighty bishop...   But unfortunately, we don't live in an ideal world!! 😀 }
3. d4
{ We immediately break through, not giving Black any time to rest on his laurels. }
3... d5
{ Black gives up the center pawn in order to quickly finish his development. }
4. dxe5 fxe5 5. e3
{ Let's not be greedy and focus on following the golden principles and finish our development first. }
5... Nc6 6. Bb5 { Continuing the assault on e5. } 6... Bd6 7. Nf3
{ Thanks to the disappearance of the d/f-pawns, White is just clearly superior here.  I would wish the viewers not to allow cheapos like  7.Qxd5  Bb4+  losing our queen! }
*

