1. b3
{ We just give Black the centre, a false sense of security... Only to take all of them back with interest at the right time! }
1... e5
{ After  1...d6  2.Bb2  Black is well advised to transpose to 1...e5 territory! }
2. Bb2 d6
{ Pay close attention to this move, as this was one of the lines... I faced a lot in Blitz/Bullet games. }
3. c4
{ I feel this is the most critical attempt, but for some reason, it is only the 3rd most popular move after e3 and g3!   This is less commital as we keep all options involving both e3 and g3 ideas open. }
3... g6 { Black wants to get Bg7-f5 etc. } 4. d4
{ We don't give Black time to execute any of his plans! 😀 } 4... Bg7 5. dxe5
{ We are heading for forcing directions  @@StartBracket@@unlike moves like e3 or Nf3@@EndBracket@@ to provoke Black into making some positional concessions! }
5... Nc6 6. Nc3 { Forcing the recapture on e5. } 6... dxe5 7. Qxd8+ Nxd8 8. Nf3
{ With a more pleasant endgame. We follow it up with long castling and Nb5/d5 etc. If Black continues with  8...c6  then White can eye the d6-square via  9.Ne4  with a clear advantage. }
