d4 { Strike them when it's hot! } 5... exd4 6. Qxd4 Bg7 7. Qe3+
{ Provoking Qe7 which gives the better endgame or Be6 where the bishop is slightly misplaced and can't head to the h1-a8 diagonal!   7.g3  O-O  is usually seen, but I think Black is not doing so bad! }
7... Be6 8. Rd1
{ One of Black's main idea is to prepare d5 in some lines due to our lazy development and hence we need to fight against it. }
