{ Thanks to some weird inconsistency in Black's pieces we get back our exchange. }
18... Bxb2 19. Nc7 { It's forking time! } 19... Bc3 20. Qxc3
{ And we will get our exchange back. Following is an example of how the game could continue:  20...Rc8  21.Bxb7  Forcing Black to take it or leave it!  21...Qxe2  22.Bxc8  Rxc8  23.Qa5  With an extra pawn for us... though Black's activity should ensure that he can drum up enough compensation to hold the balance. For instance:  23...Ne5  24.Qa6!  We can't allow the queens to prevail!  24...Nf3+  Here we have an interesting idea in mind:  25.Kg2  Nh4+  26.Kh3!!  That's how we roll!  26...Qxa6  27.Nxa6  With a slight edge. }
