{ This will lead to a slightly better version than the main line. } 3. e4 Nc6
{ With this move order, Black stops us from achieving d4 followed by Qd2 which is very advantageous for us. }
4. Nf3 Bb7 { 4...e6  5.Nc3  would eventually transpose to the same. } 5. Nc3 e6
6. d4
{ Opening up the centre to capitalize on our positional trumps and to put pressure on d6. }
6... cxd4 7. Nxd4 Nf6 8. Nxc6 { In order to facilitate our next move. } 8...
Bxc6 9. Bd3
{ We managed to blunt the c6-bishop while keeping our bishop at full power! }
9... Qc7 10. Qd2 b5 { If Black plays slowly, we have a slight pull. } 11. O-O-O
{ First getting our king to safety on the queenside, since eventually, we will have to target the Black king with pawn storms when he goes to the kingside. }
11... a6 12. Rhe1 { Bringing in our last sleeping reserve. } 12... b4 13. Nd5
{ Oh yeah! } 13... Nxd5 14. exd5 Bxd5 15. Qg5
{ What a powerful position for us with a very strong attack! } *

