[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "The Brave and The Copycat: 1.b3 b6"]
[Black "1.b3 b6 2.e4 e5 #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. b3
{ We just give Black the centre, a false sense of security... Only to take all of them back with interest at the right time! }
1... b6 { Black doesn't want to think on his own, and instead just copies us! }
2. e4
{ We muddle up Black's lazy plans. The alternative  2.Bb2  Bb7  seems quite easy for Black and frankly, not very challenging. }
2... e5 3. Nf3 Nc6 4. Bc4
{ We immediately focus on the matter at hand - the f7-square! Black really can't develop Nf6 due to the huge threat with Ng5. 😀 }
4... Bb7 5. O-O g6 6. d4
{ Striking in the center before Black has time to complete his fianchetto! }
6... exd4 7. c3
{ Opening up the position with maximum speed in order to utilize Black's development issues. }
7... dxc3 8. Nxc3 Bg7 9. Bg5
{ Is clearly winning for White due to the weak dark squares, underdeveloped pieces and weak king. For example, play could continue: }
9... Bf6 10. Bxf6 Nxf6 11. e5 Nh5 12. Qd2
{ With a winning advantage. Black can't castle as that would allow Qh6 followed by Ng5. }
*

