1. b3
{ We just give Black the centre, a false sense of security... Only to take all of them back with interest at the right time! }
1... b6 { Black doesn't want to think on his own, and instead just copies us! }
2. e4
{ We muddle up Black's lazy plans. The alternative  2.Bb2  Bb7  seems quite easy for Black and frankly, not very challenging. }
2... Bb7 3. Nc3 e5 4. Nf3 Nf6 5. Nxe5 { This looks simplest. } 5... Qe7 6. d4
{ Entering a forcing line which leads to a slightly better endgame for us. }
6... Nxe4 7. Nxe4 Bxe4 8. Bb2
{ We are not scared of the threats on the e-file. } 8... f6 9. Qe2
{ The only move... But cool enough.😀 } 9... Bb7 10. Nc4
{ The best place for the knight is on e3. } 10... Qxe2+ 11. Kxe2
{ A brave king! } 11... Nc6 12. Ne3
{ With a pleasant endgame advantage and our knight on e3 is well placed for both offensive and defensive purposes! }
