{ We have conquered the centre thanks to delaying the castling. } 7... c5 8. d5
{ We have managed to blunt the b7-bishop. } 8... e6 9. O-O
{ The d5-pawn is tactically protected. } 9... exd5 10. cxd5 d6
{ This was played by Mr. xamax which is the secret identity of Mad Max. Oh, wait... did I just reveal it to the entire world? Never mind, good luck figuring out which Max this is. 😀 }
11. Nfd2 { The knight has a glorious purpose on c4: to target the d6-pawn. }
11... Na6 { Black's best bet. } 12. Nc3 Nxd5
{ Black has to enter this tactical skirmish... if he wants to aim for equality. }
13. Nxd5 { Entering a line that is more or less forced for both sides. } 13...
Bxb2 14. Rb1 Bg7 15. Nf6+
{ Winning the exchange with this sweet discovered check. } 15... Qxf6 16. Bxb7
Nb4 17. Bxa8
{ Moves like  17.a3  would allow  17...Rab8  and the knight will survive! }
17... Rxa8 18. a3 Nc6 19. Nf3 { With an extra exchange for a pawn. } *

