1... g6 { Two can play this game! Fighting fire with fire! } 2. Bb2 Nf6 3. Nf3
Bg7 4. g3 { We just take it one step further and aim for a double fianchetto! }
4... O-O 5. Bg2
{ This is a major tabiya, and there are many ways for Black to continue here... But the true King's Indian player can play only the following move! }
5... d6 6. d4 Nbd7 7. O-O
{ White's play is very easy and he has lots of plans with simple ideas, One way is to play a4-a5 to gain space and restrict Black's forces and also c4-Nc3 with good control over the centre. }
