{ I came up with this idea to prepare e5 more leisurely from the black side. }
8. a4
{ I guess with this find, I am permanently putting an end to the Re8 line 😀... The things we do for a Chessable course. 😀 }
8... e5 9. dxe5 Ng4 10. a5 Ngxe5 11. Nxe5 Nxe5 12. Ra2
{ A hidden idea of a4.😀 The intention is to support our mighty bishop on b2 and to avoid any tactical shots like Nf3+, winning the bishop pair.   12.a6  Rb8  13.axb7  Bxb7  14.Bxb7  Rxb7  is not entirely clear. }
12... Rb8 13. c4
{ Preparing the knight outpost on d5 and increasing our space influence. }
13... Be6 14. Bd4
{ Forcing Black to make an unpleasant decision between either to play b6-opening up the a-file for our rook or a6-which permanently fixes the b7-pawn! }
14... b6 15. axb6 axb6 16. Nc3
{ Once again White's superior pieces, control over the a-file and potential exchange of dark-squared bishops which will weaken Black's king... gives the advantage to White. }
