{ If  7.d4  then  d5!  and suddenly Black seizes the advantage, since he is the one with better development and the initiative. }
7... d5 8. cxd5
{ We can never allow Black to achieve the d4 advance as that would reduce our b2-bishop's potential. }
8... Qxd5 { Is just horrible and almost close to lost after... } 9. Ne5
{ Why am I mentioning this? In case you were wondering...   It happened in one of my bullets and I didn't play Ne5! I wanted to make sure it doesn't happen to our dear viewers! 😀 }
