{ Trying to keep as many pieces as possible and also targetting one of the few weaknesses in Black's camp which is the c5-pawn before he has time to play Rb8-b6. }
11... Bxb2 12. Qxb2 Nxc4 13. Qc3
{ Let's look at sample lines as to how play could continue. } 13... Nd6 14.
Nxc5 Rb8 15. d3 { Finishing development. } 15... b6 16. Qb2 Qc7 17. Nb3 Bb7 18.
e4
{ With a slight edge due to the extra pawn in the centre which counts for something and also after h3, Black has to go Nh6. }
