5... d5 6. c4
{ Attacking the centre before Black can comfortably stabilize it. } 6... e6 7.
O-O b6 8. d4 Bb7 9. Nbd2
{ The knight is better placed here as it doesn't get in the way of our beautiful bishop on b2. }
9... Nbd7 10. Rc1 c5 11. Qc2 Rc8 12. dxc5 Nxc5 13. Qb1
{ The queen is going somewhere... } 13... Qe7 14. Qa1
{ Reti's Rifle achieved!! } 14... Rfd8 15. Rfd1
{ With a slightly more comfortable position due to the pressure along the long diagonal, if Black does get tired of it and exchanges it then the king becomes weak. }
