[Black "7...Re8 8.d4 Bg4"]
[Result "*"]

1. b3
{ We just give Black the centre, a false sense of security... Only to take all of them back with interest at the right time! }
1... Nf6 2. Bb2 g6 { 'Two can play this game!' } 3. Nf3 Bg7 4. g3
{ We just take it one step further and aim for a double fianchetto! } 4... O-O
5. Bg2
{ This is a major tabiya, there are many ways for Black to continue here. }
5... d5 6. c4
{ Attacking the centre before Black can comfortably stabilize it. } 6... c6
{ It's like Black is saying 'I am a very solid player!'... Nimzo-Larsen players would reply 'We don't care!' }
7. O-O { One prophylactic and futuristic noob went for } 7... Re8
{ which is surprisingly quite popular! } 8. d4 Bg4
{ is almost never a good idea for Black. } 9. Ne5
{ 'The bishop on g4 is bullied for no reason!' } 9... Be6 10. e3
{ A nice move stabilizing the center and clearing the path for Qe2. } 10...
Nbd7 11. Qe2
{ Supporting c4 and to be followed by Rd1-Nc3 etc with a clear edge thanks to the passively placed Black pieces. }
*

