{ Black first decides to finish his kingside development and then figure out where to put the c8-bishop. }
7. Bg2 O-O 8. O-O d5
{ Black is still biding his time and not commiting his bishop. } 9. Nc3 Bb7
{ 9...Ba6  looks weird and pointless after  10.d3  What is the bishop doing on a6? }
10. cxd5
{ Asking Black to make a decision which could affect the path of both of our lives... }
10... Nxd5 11. Nxd5
{ As a rule the structure after  10...exd5  11.d4  is advantageous for us due to the potential pressure we can exert on the center. }
11... Qxd5 12. d4 { One of the most natural moves would be } 12... Rad8 13. Ne5
{ Discovered attack from the bishop and suddenly the mighty queen starts to feel not so happy on d5. }
