[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "The English Way: 1.b3 c5 2.Bb2 Nc6"]
[Black "4.e3 e6 5.Nf3 Be7 #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. b3
{ We just give Black the centre with a false sense of security, only to take it all back with interest at the right time! }
1... c5 2. Bb2 Nc6 3. c4
{ The move order is very important, we delay Nf3 for the time being. } 3... Nf6
4. e3 { One of the toughest lines I had to fight against was the solid } 4...
e6 5. Nf3
{ After  5...d5  6.cxd5  either recapture will lead to the QGD chapter. } 5...
Be7
{ Black is fiddling with the move orders! Somehow I had to revisit many lines which I managed to avoid with the same move tricks 😀... }
6. Nc3 { One of the natural reactions for Black would be } 6... d5 7. cxd5
{ Of course we can't allow Black to achieve d4 followed by e5 which would give him the better chances. }
7... exd5 8. d4 { Same concept, stop d4 by playing d4 ourselves. } 8... O-O 9.
Be2
{ 9...Bg4  shouldn't bother us after  10.dxc5!  Just when things were getting hot around d4.  10...Bxc5  11.O-O  with a stable advantage due to the indirect control over d4. }
9... Ne4
{ Black is preparing Bf6 with nice pressure on d4 and the a1-h8 diagonal. This was my major issue...but finally after huge effort and some music on the side😀, I managed to find a nice line for us! }
10. dxc5 { Black may also go for } 10... Bf6 11. Rc1
{ One creepy attempt to win the a2-pawn is } 11... Nb4 12. Nd4
{ The lesser of evil. } 12... Nxc3 13. Rxc3 Nxa2 14. Rc2
{ Black could steer the game into an endgame with } 14... Qa5+
{ Or  14...Nb4  15.Rc1  with an interesting and fresh middlegame where I like our chances because of our strong c5-pawn and full control over the central square on d4.  15...Bd7  16.O-O  a5  17.Bf3  with good play against the d5-pawn. }
15. Qd2 { We are happy to oblige 😀 . } 15... Qxd2+ 16. Rxd2
{ with a nice endgame due to the advanced pawn on c5 and the strong knight on d4. }
*

