{ Black is fiddling with the move orders! Somehow I had to revisit many lines which I managed to avoid with the same move tricks 😀... }
6. Nc3
{ Pay close attention to the move order here, as we can avoid some good options for Black. First comes the knight! }
6... O-O 7. Be2 d5 8. cxd5 Nxd5
{ 8...exd5  9.d4  would transpose to @@StartFEN@@r1bqk2r/pp1pbppp/2n1pn2/2p5/2P5/1PN1PN2/PB1P1PPP/R2QKB1R b KQkq - 3 6@@EndFEN@@  6...d5  which we have examinedhere. }
9. Qc2
{ Giving the position a similar touch like in our QGD chapter with the only difference is that we have already commited Be2. }
9... h6 10. Nxd5
{ Opening up the long diagonal to showcase the might of our fianchetto bishop. }
10... Qxd5 11. Rd1 { Preparing d4 at our own leisure. } 11... Rd8 12. Bc4
{ Just to show that we are the superior beings. } 12... Qd6 13. O-O
{ with a pleasant middlegame thanks to the strong bishops pointing to the kingside. }
