1. b3
{ We just give Black the centre with a false sense of security, only to take it all back with interest at the right time! }
1... c5 2. Bb2 Nc6 3. c4
{ The move order is very important, we delay Nf3 for the time being. } 3... Nf6
4. e3
{ 4.Bxf6  gxf6  5.Nc3  with a strategical fight. To be honest I wouldn't mind trying this as White!  5...e6  6.e3  with a pleasant advantage.   5...h5!  Black has to do this, otherwise he gets slightly worse.  6.h4!  Fixing the pawn on h5 and making it a future target for our pieces.  6...d6  7.g3  with play on the light squares. }
4... d5
{ The principled attempt, fighting for the central control and trying to target the recently weakened d3 square. }
