[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "A Solid and Shanky Recipe: 1.b3 d5 2.Bb2 Bf5"]
[Black "2... Nf6 3.Nf3 Bg4 #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. b3
{ We just give Black the centre with a false sense of security, only to take it all back with interest at the right time! }
1... d5 2. Bb2
{ A slightly tricky and clever move order aimed against our plans would be }
2... Nf6 3. Nf3 { One natural and popular direction is } 3... Bg4 4. e3
{ As we can't commit to g3 systems anymore. } 4... Nbd7 5. h3
{ Bullying the bishop. } 5... Bh5 6. g4 { Same concept! } 6... Bg6 7. g5
{ Gaining lot of space on the kingside and lengthening the power of the b2-bishop. }
7... Ne4 8. h4 { Threatening the nasty h5. } 8... Bh5 9. Be2
{ A new direction followed by d3-Nc3 with a slightly better game for us. } *

