Bd7 5. c4 { Beginning of the center fight... } 5... Nc6
{ Black is giving priority to speedy piece development than pawn moves! } 6.
Bxf6 { This is the most testing and Black has to walk a minefield. } 6... exf6
{ Now follows a funny forced sequence. } 7. cxd5 Nb4 8. Nc3 Bg4
{ An insane idea to provoke f3. } 9. f3 { Best way to stop Nd3+. } 9... Bc8
{ Black has to threaten to capture on d5 and also keep control over the knight on h4, hence this is preferable to Bd7. }
10. e4 g5 11. a3 { Never back down. } 11... gxh4
{ After  11...Nxd5!  12.exd5  Qe7+  Black has to play very precisely to hold the balance and the following line is forced for both.  13.Kf2  Qc5+  14.d4  Qxc3  15.Bb5+  Kd8  16.Re1  Bd6  17.Rc1  Qb2+  18.Re2  Qxa3  19.Ra1  Qb4  20.Qd3  a6  21.Nf5  Bxf5  22.Qxf5  Qxd4+  23.Re3  Bg3+  24.hxg3  Qb2+  25.Re2 }
12. axb4 Bxb4 13. Qe2 { with an advantage due to the strong centre pawn mass. }
