6. e3
{ This is probably one of the few times we are going for the b3-d3-e3 setup in our entire course. After our usual approach with  6.g3  O-O  7.Bg2  Nbd7  8.O-O  Re8  looks fine for Black as he gets e5 next. }
6... O-O 7. Be2 Re8
{ After  7...Bg4  8.c4  Black has to give up his g4-bishop one day and we will just patiently wait for that day to get an edge 😀.   If Black plays  7...Bf5  we will continue with  8.O-O  followed by c4 with a good game. }
8. c4 Nbd7 9. d4 { Stopping Black's main idea even at the cost of a tempo! }
9... Ne4 10. O-O Nxd2 11. Qxd2 { with a pleasant middlegame. } *

