1. b3
{ We just give Black the centre with a false sense of security, only to take it all back with interest at the right time! }
1... d5 2. Bb2 { Some have recommended } 2... c6
{ We can also reach this position via @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1@@EndFEN@@  1.b3  c6  2.Bb2  d5 }
3. d3 { We stay adamant about our direction! } 3... Bf5 4. Nd2
{ e4 is coming! } 4... Nf6 5. g3 Nbd7
{ This is the only way to force us to play Ngf3 as otherwise Black will play e5 which is not ideal, if not for Nbd7, White can delay playing Ngf3 and continue normally with Bg2 followed by e4. }
6. Ngf3
{ As Naka would say 'It is what it is', but an early Nbd7 is not good for Black as we are in time to achieve e4. }
6... e6 7. Bg2 Bg6 8. O-O Bc5 9. e4
{ It is important to remember that whenever Black hasn't castled, We can go e4 without having to play Re1 or Qe1...Since it is tactically defended due to the pressure along the long diagonal. }
