1. b3
{ We just give Black the centre with a false sense of security, only to take it all back with interest at the right time! }
1... d5 2. Bb2 Bf5 3. d3 { A recently approved direction by Nepo. } 3... Nf6 4.
Nd2 c5 { Otherwise we will eventually reach a transposition. } 5. e4
{ Fast and the furious! } 5... dxe4 6. dxe4 Nxe4 7. Bd3
{ Giving up a pawn for quick development. } 7... Nd6 8. Bxf5 Nxf5 9. Qf3
{ A nice double attack! } 9... Qc8 10. O-O-O Nc6 11. Ne2
{ with full compensation for the pawn and some sample lines are } 11... e6 12.
Ne4 Be7 13. g4 Nfd4 { Black has to give up the pawn. } 14. Nxd4 Nxd4 15. Bxd4
{ 'Captures, captures and captures' - Agadmator. } 15... cxd4 16. Rxd4
{ I didn't really want to recommend this positon at first, due to our weak king... }
16... O-O 17. Rhd1
{ I understood that thanks to the strong knight on e4 and well coordinated pieces, we are not in any danger at all! }
17... Qc6 18. g5 { The knight on e4 will remain untouched. } 18... Rfc8
{ 18...a5  19.a4  puts an abrupt end to Black's silly attacking ambitions. }
19. Qd3
{ followed by Kb2 and Black can't create any form of play! We have many plans like h4, Rd7 etc. }
*

