[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "The Magician's Path: 1.b3 d5 2.Bb2 Bg4"]
[Black "2...Bg4 3.f3 Bc8"]
[Result "*"]

1. b3 d5 2. Bb2 Bg4 3. f3 Bc8 4. d4
{ The only way to fight for an advantage, thanks to the two extra tempos we have. If white goes for 4. e4, Black is fine after 4...e6. }
4... Nf6
{ If Black tries to lash out with  4...c5  We coolly reply with  5.e4!  Fighting for central control.  5...dxe4   @@StartBracket@@Black is well advised to play  5...Nf6  which will lead to transposition to the mainline after  6.Nc3  @@EndBracket@@  6.d5!  A very central thrust gaining the space and full control over the position.  6...exf3  7.Nxf3  Black's position is looking horrible, as literally as his entire army is sleeping.  7...Nf6  8.Bb5+!  An important move to exchange the light-squared bishop.  8...Bd7  9.Bxd7+  Nbxd7   if  9...Qxd7  the  10.Nc3  with a winning advantage due to Black's poor development.  10.O-O  with a clear advantage and the pawn deficit is barely felt due to Black's lack of space. }
5. Nc3 c5
{ Trying to gain the center.  5...e6  6.e4  c5  would transpose to  6...e6  lines }
6. e4 Nc6
{ If Black goes for the lame  6...e6  7.exd5!  Making sure that the d5-pawn will remain a target for our pieces.  7...exd5  8.Nge2  Nc6  9.Qd2  followed by long castling with a solid advantage due to better development and isolated pawn on  d5  . }
7. dxc5 e6 8. exd5 Nxd5 9. Nxd5
{ This is the only way to fight for an advantage. } 9... exd5 10. Qe2+
{ We need to protect the c5-pawn at any cost. } 10... Be6 11. Qf2 d4
{ It was worth making Black commit this move, as this pawn becomes a future target for us.  If Black goes for   11...Qa5+  12.Qd2  is slightly better for White. }
12. O-O-O Bxc5 13. Bd3 { The best place for the bishop. } 13... Qa5
{ 13...O-O  14.Ne2  would also lead to similar positions like in the mainline. }
14. Kb1 Nb4 { Forcing an exchange operation. } 15. a3 Nxd3 16. Rxd3 Bxa3
{ Only move, since b4 was a serious threat. } 17. Ne2 O-O 18. Nxd4 Bxb2 19.
Kxb2
{ with a very minute pull for White, due to more active pieces and the superior material imbalance of Q+N vs Q+B which would arise after the exchange of the rooks. }
*

