[Black "2...Bg4 3.f3 Bf5 4.e4 dxe4 5.Nc3 exf3 6.Qxf3 e6 #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. b3
{ We just give Black the centre, a false sense of security... Only to take all of them back with interest at the right time! }
1... d5 2. Bb2 Bg4
{ was the preference of my childhood hero-Mikhal Tal. Black is cutting into White's plans of development. }
3. f3
{ We answer in style! One of the hidden advantages of not commiting Nf3! Attacking the bishop and clearing the path for e4. }
3... Bf5 4. e4 { Attacking the centre with maximum force! } 4... dxe4 5. Nc3
{ The greedy } 5... exf3 6. Qxf3 e6 { Trying to give up the pawn and survive. }
7. Qxb7 { Black's pawn structure is permanently ruined. } 7... Nd7 8. O-O-O
{ Black is doing reasonable if he can finish his development and get his king to safety... So we are obilged to strike before that. }
8... Rb8 9. Qf3 { Preparing g4. } 9... Ngf6 10. Nge2 { Finishing development. }
10... Bd6 11. h3 { followed by g4 with advantage. } *

