8... e6 9. g5 Nd5 10. Qb5+
{ Forcing Black to play Nd7 which in turn loses control over d5. } 10... Nd7
11. Nxd5 { Of course taking on b7 was never our intention :@@EndBracket@@! }
11... Be4 { A strong double attack! } 12. Qe2
{ Our priority is to keep the intiative. } 12... Bxd5 13. O-O-O
{ Safety time! } 13... a5
{ Black is finding his chance by creating his own play against our king. } 14.
c4 Bc6 15. Kc2 { In order to prepare d4. } 15... a4 16. d4
{ with a messy fight with chances for both sides. } *

