1. b3
{ We just give Black the centre, a false sense of security... Only to take all of them back with interest at the right time! }
1... d5 2. Bb2 Bg4
{ was the preference of my childhood hero-Mikhal Tal. Black is cutting into White's plans of development. }
3. f3
{ We answer in style! One of the hidden advantages of not commiting Nf3! Attacking the bishop and clearing the path for e4. }
3... Bf5 4. e4 { Attacking the centre with maximum force! } 4... dxe4 5. Nc3
{ I love it, when we sacrifice pawns for sake of fast development and intiative! }
5... Nf6 6. g4
{ Making our intentions very clear, we are just gonna roll over the kingside with pawn storms! }
6... Bg6 7. Qe2 { Clearing the path to safety for the king. } 7... exf3 8. Nxf3
{ For a pawn we have managed to open two important e and f-files which can be used for our attacking purposes. }
8... e6 9. g5 Nh5 10. Qb5+
{ Generally I wouldn't advocate such an approach...but here it is mandatory to ruin Black's pawn structure. }
10... Nd7 11. Qxb7 Rb8 12. Qa6
{ Let's not take on a7, as we intend to go long castling. } 12... Bd6 13. O-O-O
O-O 14. Re1 { with an epic fight! } *

