[Result "*"]

1. b3
{ We just give Black the centre, a false sense of security... Only to take all of them back with interest at the right time! }
1... d5 2. Bb2 c5
{ Black starts the fight for the centre. I came up with the name Ozmin Attack @@StartBracket@@which is just Nimzo put in reverse order@@EndBracket@@ thanks to the help of my discord members 😀. }
3. e3
{ The bishop is usually best placed on b5 in order to fight for the control of the e5-square. }
3... e6 { Black is keeping all his options open. } 4. Nf3 Nc6 5. Bb5 Ne7
{ One of the ideas of delaying Nf6. } 6. c4
{ Trying to hold on to the bishop for the time being. } 6... a6 7. Ba4 Bd7
{ 7...f6  8.O-O  and White was better in Granda-Diaz 2015 } 8. O-O
{ The last seen } 8... Nf5 { allows } 9. cxd5
{ We need to utilize our lead in development and this is the best way to do it. }
9... exd5 10. Bxc6
{ This is not so easy to understand, but it gives a big advantage for us. }
10... Bxc6
{ If  10...bxc6  the  11.Nc3  followed by easy play attacking the weak pawns on c6/c6 by Rc1-Na4. }
11. Ne5 { followed by Qh5 ideas which would put Black in a difficult spot. }
11... Bd6
{ The passive  11...Be7  does not help either as after  12.Nxc6  bxc6  Black's structure is ruined.  13.Nc3  O-O  14.Na4  with a clear advantage. }
12. Nxc6 bxc6 13. Qg4 { The best square for the queen. } 13... Qd7 14. Nc3
{ with a clear advantage due to the easy targets on the c-file. } *

