[White "Ozmin Attack: 1.b3 d5 2.Bb2 c5"]
[Black "3.e3 e6 #3"]
[Result "*"]

1. b3
{ We just give Black the centre, a false sense of security... Only to take all of them back with interest at the right time! }
1... d5 2. Bb2 c5
{ Black starts the fight for the centre. I came up with the name Ozmin Attack @@StartBracket@@which is just Nimzo put in reverse order@@EndBracket@@ thanks to the help of my discord members 😀. }
3. e3
{ The bishop is usually best placed on b5 in order to fight for the control of the e5-square. }
3... e6 { Black is keeping all his options open. } 4. Nf3 Nc6 5. Bb5 Bd7 6. c4
{ We follow this concept of targeting Black's center before he completes his development. }
6... a6 7. Bxc6 Bxc6 8. Ne5
{ Winning back the bishop and also increasing our influence in the center. }
8... Rc8
{ 8...Qc7  will be met with  9.Qf3!  stopping Black's usual development plan with Ng8-f6 which would be met by taking the bishop on  c6  and  Bxf6  , winning the pawn.  9...f6  can be tried but it offers little help because  10.Qh5  g6  11.Nxg6!  Utilising the pin along the h-file.  11...Qf7  12.cxd5!  A useful inclusion to clarify matters in the center.  12...exd5  13.Nf4  with a healthy extra pawn. }
9. O-O Nf6 10. d3
{ Leads to a transposition to the mainline of Ozmin Attack here } *

