1. b3
{ We just give Black the centre, a false sense of security... Only to take all of them back with interest at the right time! }
1... d5 2. Bb2 c5
{ Black starts the fight for the centre. I came up with the name Ozmin Attack @@StartBracket@@which is just Nimzo put in reverse order@@EndBracket@@ thanks to the help of my discord members 😀. }
3. e3
{ The bishop is usually best placed on b5 in order to fight for the control of the e5-square. }
3... Nc6 4. Bb5
{ Given a choice,we always go for this placement for the bishop as it helps us fight for the e5-square. }
4... e6 5. Bxc6+
{ Before Black changes his mind and protects the knight with a piece 😀! } 5...
bxc6 { Black's structure will remain like this for a while! } 6. d3 Nh6 7. Nd2
{ Preventing any c4 ideas which would liberate Black's structure. } 7... f6 8.
f4 { This is how we fight for the control of e5-square. } 8... Bd6
{ As you can see both sides are fighting for the same thing. } 9. Qh5+
{ The queen will be well placed on the kingside and it also controls e5. } 9...
Nf7 10. O-O-O a5 11. a4
{ Of course we can never allow Black to achieve a4 in this structure, We have a slightly better middlegame due to the better pawn structure. }
