[Black "5.Nf3 Nf6 6.c4 Nb4 #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. b3
{ We just give Black the centre, a false sense of security... Only to take all of them back with interest at the right time! }
1... d5 2. Bb2 c5
{ Black starts the fight for the centre. I came up with the name Ozmin Attack @@StartBracket@@which is just Nimzo put in reverse order@@EndBracket@@ thanks to the help of my discord members 😀. }
3. e3
{ The bishop is usually best placed on b5 in order to fight for the control of the e5-square. }
3... Nc6 4. Bb5
{ Given a choice,we always go for this placement for the bishop as it helps us fight for the e5-square. }
4... Bd7 5. Nf3 Nf6 6. c4
{ We strike the centre before Black is fully ready!   An alternative is  6.O-O  g6!  wasn't so easy to crack and I felt play wasn't so challenging for Black.  7.Nc3   7.Bxf6  is not very promising because of  exf6  8.Nc3  a6!  Forcing us to take on  c6  or to relax the pressure on the a4-e8 diagonal.  9.Bxc6  Bxc6  with slight advantage to Black!  7...a6!  We are forced to give up our beautiful pair.  8.Bxc6  Bxc6  9.d4!  could be another way to play. }
6... Nb4
{ is just silly! Black is not developed enough to embark on such antics 😀. } 7.
d4 { The arkham assault on center begins! } 7... cxd4
{ 7...Bxb5  8.cxb5  would only get the b4-knight into trouble!  8...c4  9.bxc4  dxc4  10.Ne5  The c4-pawn will fall and with that we will gain a huge advantage in addition to positional trumps like centre majority. }
8. a3 { GO BACK! } 8... Nc6 9. O-O { Best is } 9... e6
{ 9...dxe3  10.cxd5  exf2+  11.Rxf2  Nb8  12.Bc4!  Let's not help Black.  12...b5  13.Bd3  with a winning advantage thanks to the superior pieces and Black has developed only one piece.     Another greedy line is  9...dxc4  10.exd4!  cxb3  11.d5  with clear domination on the center. }
10. exd4 Be7 11. c5
{ Potentially we can consider creating a passed pawn on the queenside by continuing with b4-a4 and advance the pawns. }
*

