[White "Queens Gambit Declined: 1.b3 d5 2.Bb2 Nf6-e6"]
[Black " 1.b3 d5 2.Bb2 Nf6 3.Nf3 e6  4.c4 c5 #8"]
[Result "*"]

1. b3
{ We just give Black the centre, a false sense of security... Only to take all of them back with interest at the right time! }
1... d5 2. Bb2 Nf6 { So far I am fine with what Black is doing. } 3. Nf3 e6
{ Here my issues start 😀. Many people just have a strict and lazy repertoire and they just go for d5-Nf6-e6-Be7 against just every possible line 😀...But let's not judge them and I would even say 'Lazy people are not bad people' AD 2020. }
4. c4
{ One of the topical direction for Black which could arise via many orders is }
4... c5 { And only now do we go for a transposition to the mainlines with } 5.
e3
{ It is always nice to keep the tension in the center...for as long as possible. }
5... Nc6 6. cxd5 exd5 { Major tabiya in recent times. } 7. d4
{ An exciting direction which poses lots of practical issues for Black to solve. }
7... cxd4 8. Nxd4
{ 8...Bb4+  is the mainline. Black's only other move which challenges us is }
8... Ne4
{ The usual  8...Bd6  shouldn't bother us, as we have achieved inner peace and mastery of d4-square.  9.Be2  O-O  10.O-O  Re8  11.Nd2  I don't like to repeat myself...but I will make an exception for the sake of this course! 'Control, blockade and destroy!' - Nimzowitch. Focus your play against the Isolani on d5. }
9. a3 { Stopping any Bb4 checks...once and for all! } 9... Qh4 10. g3 Qf6
{ A funky line but we are doing fine after } 11. Qc2 Bd7
{ Another line would be  11...Nxd4  12.Bxd4  Qf3  13.Bb5+!  Just in time!  13...Bd7  14.Bxd7+  Kxd7  15.O-O  Castling is saved!  15...Ng5  16.h4!  and Black is not able to do anything more on the kingside leading to a stable advantage for us. }
12. Bb5 { Just continue development, as simple as that! } 12... Rc8
{ Moving away from the annoying diagonal and the threats of our mighty bishop.   12...Qg6  13.Nd2!  Development!  13...Nxd4  14.Bxd7+  Kxd7  Losing the castling rights.  15.Bxd4  Rc8  16.Qd3  with a slightly more comfortable game thanks to ideas like  Qb5+  and usual play against the isolani. }
13. Nxc6 Qf3 { Moving out of the discovered attack in style! } 14. Rf1
{ Only move for us. } 14... Bxc6
{ The lame  14...bxc6  would give us the edge after  15.Ba6!  Rb8  16.b4  followed by Nd2 or Be2 ideas. }
15. Nd2 Qf5
{ Worse is  15...Nxd2  16.Be2!  This is such an amazing retreat in order to facilitate Qxd2.  16...Qe4  17.Qxd2    with clear advantage due to the better bishops and pawn structure. }
16. Bd3
{ with a slight pull and we follow it up with Rc1 playing with our king in the centre! }
