[Round "?"]
[White "Queens Gambit Declined: 1.b3 d5 2.Bb2 Nf6-e6"]
[Black " 1.b3 d5 2.Bb2 Nf6 3.Nf3 e6  4.c4 c5 #9"]
[Result "*"]

1. b3
{ We just give Black the centre, a false sense of security... Only to take all of them back with interest at the right time! }
1... d5 2. Bb2 Nf6 { So far I am fine with what Black is doing. } 3. Nf3 e6
{ Here my issues start 😀. Many people just have a strict and lazy repertoire and they just go for d5-Nf6-e6-Be7 against just every possible line 😀...But let's not judge them and I would even say 'Lazy people are not bad people' AD 2020. }
4. c4
{ One of the topical direction for Black which could arise via many orders is }
4... c5 { And only now do we go for a transposition to the mainlines with } 5.
e3
{ It is always nice to keep the tension in the center...for as long as possible. }
5... Nc6 6. cxd5 exd5 { Major tabiya in recent times. } 7. d4
{ An exciting direction which poses lots of practical issues for Black to solve. }
7... cxd4 8. Nxd4 Bb4+ 9. Bc3
{ Black has to be very precise here, as the natural moves would allow us to get the edge due to the isolated pawn. }
9... a5 { s } 10. a3
{ Of course we are not gonna take on b4 and help him activate his a8-rook also gaining control of the c3-square. }
10... Be7
{ A funky move would be  10...Bg4!?  11.Be2!  Exchanges are fine, as long as they help us in our development!  11...Bxe2  12.Nxe2  with good control over the game and centre. Officially we have no complaints and can get a slight edge.   One of the easiest lines for us would be  10...Bxc3+  11.Nxc3  We have a nice advantage thanks to the knight on  d4  .  11...O-O  12.Be2  The bishop will be well placed on f3.  12...Be6  13.O-O  Put a bishop on f3, play Nce2-f4 and double on the d-file with the rooks...do the right thing guys!   10...Bc5  11.Nxc6!  The pressure on d4 was getting too hot to handle!  11...bxc6  As proven before, we should welcome both Isolani and hanging pawn structures.  12.Bd3  O-O  13.O-O  followed by Nd2 with a nice game and play against the hanging pawns. }
11. Nd2 { No Ne4 for black! } 11... O-O 12. Be2
{ with good chances to get something real and also b5-square is a nice spot for the knight on d4 if needed. }
*

