1. b3 Nf6 2. Bb2 g6 { In bullets at the beginning I used to go for } 3. f4
{ This was my favourite bullet weapon! } 3... Bg7 4. Nf3 O-O 5. e3 c5 6. Be2
Nc6 7. O-O d6 8. c4
{ Important to control some squares before going for Nc3 and to prepare Qc2. }
8... e5 9. fxe5 Ng4 10. Nc3 Ngxe5 11. Nxe5 Nxe5 12. Qc2
{ The queen is nicely placed on c2 and my idea was to continue with Nd5 trying to exchange the dark squared bishop. }
12... Bf5 { Big mistake! } 13. Rxf5 gxf5 14. Qxf5 Qf6 15. Qh3 Qg6 16. Rf1 f5
17. Nd5 { All my pieces are doing so well! } 17... Rae8 18. Bh5 Qg5 19. Bxe8 *

